  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe debugger `l` flag allows me to show source context around the current line and specify how many lines before and after: (ex: `l +5 -5`). As I step around, I can invoke `l` again and it will remember the + and - values that I have provided.  However, to continually see this context, I have to keep invoking `l` again with every new step.  It would be really nice if this value were simply stored for the entire session, so that every step displayed the full context range.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open a debugger session `truffle debug 0xabc...`\r\n2. Print additional context: `l +5 -5` \r\n3. Step next: `n`\r\n4. Notice the debugger defaults back to displaying 1 line above and below the current.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nRetain the +5 -5 context for the entire session.  I shouldn't have to keep typing `l` with every new step.  \r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nIt displays 1 line above and below.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.32\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v14.18.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.5.0\r\n",
