    "body": "At the moment, it seems that:\r\nRunning `n` (or any step) defaults to the equivalent to running `l -2 +0`. \r\nRunning `l` by itself defaults to the equivalent to running `l -5 +3`.\r\n\r\nIf we were to introduce the behavior described here, running `l` alone **_could_** still exist and default to these values if we wanted it to.  Running `l` alone would essentially override whatever values you set previously and display `-5 +3` for all steps moving forward.",
